u gain party experience!!<BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>He poofs and you have the new pearl in your inventory.<P>  <IMG SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~dossey97/pictures/pearl.jpg">  <P>We went to Skyfire and killed the named cycle once, just out of curiousity and hope that he would be up.  So far he wasn't.  But you can be sure I will be spending some time in Skyfire.  *chuckles*<P>Back to ONE step away from my epic!  Whoohoo!<P><BR>~Angel<p>[This message has been edited by Angelyca (edited 01-24-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bagst</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for the update  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Bagst Spiritmaker<BR>Sword of Fate<BR>Prexus<P>------------------<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sirgossamer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"Ragefire was to the right of the ramp. Sitting by himself. It took us a second to see where he is. (you have to jump off the side of the ramp to reach him)"<P>Which ramp ?  The ramp where the switch lever is ?  The ramp inside Naggy's Lair (thought they were going to seperate him from Naggy encounters) ?<P>Thanks in advance for better clarification. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Angelyca</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>As you walk up to the FGs.<P>You will likely need to kill one or two FGs.  But you do not need to kill the King, or anything like that.<P>So you lev across the lava.. kill those 1-2 FGs right there.  Do *not* go inside the building.  Walk up along the right side.. there is a ramp.. look over the lava to your right and he will be sitting there.   Under a window from the Kings Chambers.<P>Lev across the lava, hand in your pearl.. and consider yourself one step closer.<P>~Angel<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kornaena</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">After I "swim" from LDC to the ledge.  UP on the ledge, is a opening that that leads to 2 FG, which continue to caverns with more LDC.  To the right of that door is a ramp that leads to a door/gate, inside that door is 2FG.  Beyond that room is stairs into king's throne room.  <P>The new ragefire is on the ledge before the door/gate to kings throne room?  IE the ledge across the lava(that I swim through) opposite the ledge with FG on it?<P>Had my ranger exping all day in sol b no luck.  Naggy was up though  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  Thanks in advance.  <P>------------------<BR>Baroness Kornaena D'Lez<BR>Dark Elven High Priestess<BR>Mith Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dokkon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just wanted to add this part. I was with Angel during the hand-in and took a shot of where he spawns. The smaller picture gives an idea of where the shot exactly is. The small map is stolen from <A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com" TARGET=_blank>EQAtlas</A> because the maps there rule.<P> <IMG SRC="http://rob.shiftclick.net/eq/newragespawn.jpg"> <P><BR> <IMG SRC="http://rob.shiftclick.net/eq/newragespawn2.jpg"> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eforty_Ounce</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Now that's what I am talking about!  Nice picture and grats to Angelyca!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Angelyca</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>*smiles*  Thanks Dokkon... and thanks folks that said grats hehe.  <P>I want to point out -- Naggy *WAS* up the entire time.  I know rumors fly about him still being linked to Naggy.  He certainly isn't.<P>Currently I am camping the Skyfire spawn *oof*  As soon as I have any info there we will post the pictures *smiles*<P>~Angel</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shyntlara Kenafin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great info turned in at 830 pm last night in skyfire now ill post again when and if i get the killable version</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vilox00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is anyone aware if it is safe to sit where rage spawns without aggroing FG repops?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hakadek - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had no problems sitting there with a full FG pop, just be careful if people start clearing them. <P>King Tranix can decide you are a good target if people do the usual trick of pulling him down the ramp to kill him.<P>Edit : I withdraw that, take great care when the FG's start re-popping, till they get settled down they can and will jump across the Lava to attack you, especially if you are below 60 and sitting down, so remain standing.<P>This will make sense when you are there, but if you go to the far end of the ledge that leads to the spawn point to the spot where you have to duck, you can still watch the spawn yet be far enough away not to agro wandering FG's, I wouldn't sit down there while they are moving around though.<P>Hakadek<p>[This message has been edited by Hakadek - Veeshan (edited 01-26-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kanroc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes indeed, sitting down on the ledge is bad.  Not that I'd know anything about going afk sitting there and coming back to Skarlon and 2 of his best friends administering a beatdown.<P>Like was already said, standing on the ledge where you have to duck seems relatively safe (roamer didn't agro at 59)<P>--Kanroc<B